<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[811,1456,1651,2027]" box="[813,933,1651,1677]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">REMARQUE</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[811,1456,1651,2027]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">
Ces trois spécimens sont bien annotés de la main d’E. Fournier, mais notre choix s’est porté sur le spécimen 
<emphasis box="[1285,1455,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Ghiesbreght 407</emphasis>
comme 
<typeStatus box="[899,1000,1746,1772]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">lectotype</typeStatus>
, car il constitue le matériel le plus complet pour ce taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[811,1456,1651,2027]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">
Les spécimens 
<emphasis box="[1013,1188,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Bourgeau 3615</emphasis>
et 
<emphasis box="[1230,1362,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Schiede s.n.</emphasis>
ont été déterminés comme 
<taxonomicName authority="(Desv.) Proctor" authorityName="Proctor" authorityYear="1953" baseAuthorityName="Desv." box="[1041,1455,1841,1868]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Thelypteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="resinifera">
<emphasis box="[1041,1272,1841,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Thelypteris resinifera</emphasis>
(Desv.) Proctor
</taxonomicName>
par A.R. Smith en 1976. 
<taxonomicName authority="E. Fourn." authorityName="E. Fourn." box="[1092,1455,1873,1900]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Aspidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ghiesbreghtii">
<emphasis box="[1092,1340,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Aspidium ghiesbreghtii</emphasis>
E. Fourn.
</taxonomicName>
est actuellement considéré comme synonyme de 
<taxonomicName authority="(Desv.) Proctor" authorityName="Proctor" authorityYear="1953" baseAuthorityName="Desv." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Thelypteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="resinifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Thelypteris resinifera</emphasis>
(Desv.) Proctor
</taxonomicName>
par 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[1218,1370,1937,1963]" firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" pagination="35 - 55" refId="ref6046" refString="SMITH A. R. 1981. - Asplenium, in Flora of Chiapas, Part 2: Pteridophytes. California Academy of Sciences 35 - 55." type="book chapter" year="1981">Smith (1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[1386,1446,1937,1963]" firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 148" refId="ref6074" refString="SMITH A. R. 1983. - Flora d'Ecuador 14 (4). Polypodiaceae-Thelypteridoideae. Stockholm, Sweden 18: 1 - 148." type="journal article" year="1983">1983</bibRefCitation>
) et par 
<bibRefCitation author="Mickel &amp; Smith" box="[890,1175,1969,1995]" firstAuthor="Mickel" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 1054" refId="ref5937" refString="MICKEL J. T. &amp; SMITH A. R. 2004. - The Pteridophytes of Mexico. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 88: 1 - 1054." type="journal article" year="2004">Mickel &amp; Smith (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. Nous confirmons cette synonymie.
</paragraph>
